# Load Dictionary into IndexedDB with API Fallback

## Overview

Load the `dictionary_compact.json` (~22MB, flat `{word: definition}` format) into **IndexedDB** on first install/launch. Use an **in-memory cache** for recently looked-up words to avoid repeated DB reads. If a word is not found locally, fall back to the **Free Dictionary API** (`https://api.dictionaryapi.dev/api/v2/entries/en/{word}`). Remove all locale detection logic — this is **English-only**.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The `dictionary_compact.json` file is **22MB**. It will be bundled as a static asset in the extension and loaded into IndexedDB on first install. This is a one-time cost, but the extension's download size will increase by ~22MB.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The second URL you mentioned (`https://translation-1e79fb3f3adb.herokuapp.com/`) — should this be used as a translation API, or only as a secondary fallback for definitions? For now, I'm only using the Free Dictionary API as fallback. Let me know if you want to integrate the Heroku endpoint too, and how.

## Proposed Changes

### Background Service Worker

#### [MODIFY] [background.ts](file:///Users/md.khaledbin/Practices/Chrome%20Extensions/Focus/src/background.ts)

Complete rewrite of the background script:

1. **Remove** all locale detection logic (`chrome.i18n.getAcceptLanguages`, `fetchSmallDictionary`, etc.)
2. **Add IndexedDB helper** — open/create a database `FocusDictDB` with an object store `words` (key: word, value: definition)
3. **On Install** (`chrome.runtime.onInstalled`):
   - Check if IndexedDB already has data (flag in `chrome.storage.local`)
   - If not, fetch `dictionary_compact.json` from `chrome.runtime.getURL()`, parse it, and **batch-insert** all entries into IndexedDB
   - Set a flag `dictionaryLoaded: true` in `chrome.storage.local`
4. **In-memory cache**: A `Map<string, string>` for recently looked-up words (LRU-style, max ~500 entries)
5. **Word lookup** (`handleWordLookup`):
   - Check in-memory cache first → return if found
   - Check IndexedDB → return if found, add to cache
   - Fall back to Free Dictionary API (`https://api.dictionaryapi.dev/api/v2/entries/en/{word}`)
   - If API returns a result, **also store it in IndexedDB** for future offline use

