---

### Manifest (no changes needed)

The manifest already has `unlimitedStorage` permission which is needed for IndexedDB with large data.

## Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A[User selects text] --> B[Content Script sends LOOKUP_WORD]
    B --> C[Background: Check In-Memory Cache]
    C -->|Hit| D[Return Definition]
    C -->|Miss| E[Check IndexedDB]
    E -->|Hit| F[Add to Cache & Return]
    E -->|Miss| G[Fetch from Free Dictionary API]
    G -->|Found| H[Store in IndexedDB + Cache & Return]
    G -->|Not Found| I[Return null - No definition]
    
    J[Extension Install] --> K[Load dictionary_compact.json]
    K --> L[Batch insert into IndexedDB]
    L --> M[Set dictionaryLoaded flag]
```

## Open Questions

1. **Heroku Translation API**: Should `https://translation-1e79fb3f3adb.herokuapp.com/` be used? If so, when and how? (As a second fallback? For translations vs definitions?)
2. **Progress indicator**: During first-time import of the 22MB dictionary, should we show a progress bar in the popup, or is a simple "Loading..." sufficient?

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Build with `npm run build`
- Load the `dist/` folder as an unpacked extension in Chrome
- Verify IndexedDB gets populated on first install (check via DevTools → Application → IndexedDB)
- Look up a word present in the local dictionary → confirm it returns instantly from IndexedDB
- Look up a rare/missing word → confirm it falls back to the API
- Reload the extension → confirm it doesn't re-import (uses the `dictionaryLoaded` flag)
